= Code Listings

The tool is written in Python. The core compilation step:

```python
import subprocess, tempfile
from pathlib import Path

def compile_to_svgs(typ_path):
    with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmp:
        out = Path(tmp) / "page-{p}.svg"
        subprocess.run(
            ["typst", "compile", str(typ_path), str(out), "--format", "svg"],
            check=True,
        )
        return [f.read_text() for f in sorted(Path(tmp).glob("page-*.svg"))]
```

= Conclusion

typst-to-web leverages the full power of the official Typst compiler, producing
pixel-perfect SVG output that is then wrapped in a rich, interactive HTML
viewer with:

+ Full-text search across all pages
+ Table of contents with click-to-navigate
+ Dark / light mode toggle
+ Zoom controls and keyboard navigation
+ Print-friendly output
+ Zero external runtime dependencies

All Typst features — including complex math (@eq-gaussian, @eq-euler), cetz
figures (@fig-parabola), and custom packages — are rendered correctly because we
use the real compiler.

